# SliceMatic — Cursor Rules

## Start Every Session by Reading The Wiki

Canonical wiki path: `FullStack/wiki/` (not repo-root `wiki/`).
Always read `FullStack/wiki/index.md` and `FullStack/wiki/handoff.md` before material work.
Active next queue: `FullStack/plans/2026-07-21-next-horizon-sprint-plan.md`.

## Critical Rules

### Customer / Admin Shells (updated 2026-07-21)

- Customer workspace: `FullStack/components/CustomerShell.tsx` via `app/page.tsx`
- Admin workspace: `FullStack/app/admin-dashboard/page.tsx`
- Shared UI lives under `FullStack/features/*` and `FullStack/components/*`
- `SliceMaticStage3.tsx` is **deleted**. Do not recreate dual-file sync against it.
- EntryPortal (`/`) is the sole login form for all user types.

### Styling

- Legacy styles live in `FullStack/app/globals.css`
- Prefer semantic tokens and `sui-*` primitives
- Tailwind CSS v4 is allowed only through a deliberate design-system bridge (see `wiki/css-system.md`). Do not sprinkle random utility soup on legacy screens.

### TypeScript & State

- Types are in `lib/types.ts` — never redeclare inline
- Global state via Zustand (`lib/store.ts`) — sessionStorage persisted
- Auth state via sessionStorage keys — see `wiki/auth-flows.md` / `lib/session/storageKeys.ts`
- Never use `localStorage` for auth identity (Cashfree pending payment handoff may use localStorage)

### Supabase

- Guard DB calls with `hasSupabaseEnv()` / `hasSupabaseAdminEnv()` or null client checks
- Fall back to `lib/seed-data.ts` for menu data
- Do not edit `supabase/schema.sql` casually — R13/R12 forbid schema changes; S0 requires ADR + migrations

### Business Rules (`lib/pricing.ts`)

- GST = 18%, Bulk discount = 10% at qty ≥ 5, Max qty = 10
- Bill order: subtotal → discount → taxable → GST → delivery → total

## After Every Session

1. Update affected `FullStack/wiki/*.md` pages
2. Update `wiki/handoff.md` and append `wiki/log.md`
3. Update `FullStack/CHANGELOG.md` for code changes

## Never Do

- Never invent Delivery/Rider/ETA UI without real delivery schema
- Never hardcode menu prices or item names
- Never use localStorage for auth
- Never let exceptions bubble to the UI uncaught
- Never modify `gradio-MVP/` or `GRADIO-MVP-2/` for Stage 3 work

## Commands

```bash
# Working dir: FullStack/
npm run dev
npm run test
npm run build
```
